Processing the data

library(tidyverse)
library(Hmisc)
data <- read_csv("cloze_task_results.csv", show_col_types = FALSE)
data %>%
  group_by(text)%>%
  summarise(
    key_word=text,
    response=response,
    sum_count = sum(count),
    count = count
  )%>%
filter(count==max(count, na.rm = T))%>%
mutate(prop_top_answ=count/sum_count)%>%
ungroup()%>%
  mutate(extracted=str_extract(text, "\\b(kein|keine)\\b\\s+\\w+"))->mod_data
`summarise()` has grouped output by 'text'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.
# previous (bad but working) attempt at exraction...  
# separate(col=key_word, into = c("text1", "text2"), sep = "\\b(ist|sind)\\b\\s+", remove = TRUE)%>%
#  select(-c(text, text1))%>%
#  separate(col=text2, into = c("key_word", "text"), sep = ", sondern", remove = TRUE)%>%
#  select(-text) -> mod_data

mod_data$count_groups <- cut2(mod_data$count,g=37)
mod_data$count_groups <-factor(mod_data$count_groups, levels = rev(levels(mod_data$count_groups)))

Visualising the data

mod_data %>%
  filter(count>15 & count<=20) %>% 
  mutate(key_w=fct_reorder(extracted, count)) -> plot_mod_data
the_title = str_c("Top responses with count > ",min(plot_mod_data$count, na.rm = T), " & count <= ",max(plot_mod_data$count, na.rm = T))

geom.text.size = 3
theme.size = (14/5) * geom.text.size

ggplot(plot_mod_data, aes(x=key_w,y=count, fill=count_groups))+
  geom_col()+
  labs(title = str_wrap(the_title, 50), fill=str_wrap("Count (grouped)"))+
  ylim(0, 41)+
  #facet_wrap(vars(count_groups), scales = "free")+
  coord_flip()+
  xlab("") +
  ylab("Count")+
  geom_text(aes(x=key_w, y=0, label=str_c("sondern ", str_to_title(response))), size=geom.text.size, fontface="bold", hjust="left")+
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(face="bold", color="black",size=theme.size),
        axis.text.y = element_text(face="bold", color="black",size=theme.size))+
  theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5))
